Rust equivalents found:
  - emRefTarget::Alloc/Free/GetRefCount -> Rc<T> internal refcount (implicit, no explicit calls)
  - emRef<T> -> Rc<T> or Rc<RefCell<T>> throughout the codebase
    - emScreen.rs:165: Rc<RefCell<emScreen>> for LookupInherited return
    - emScreen.rs:188: Rc<RefCell<emScreen>> for Install parameter
    - emFpPlugin.rs:445: Rc<RefCell<Self>> for Acquire return
    - emCoreConfig.rs:215: Rc<RefCell<emConfigModel<Self>>> for Acquire return
    - emContext.rs:40: Weak<emContext> for parent reference (Weak = non-owning Rc)
    - emFontCache.rs:30: DIVERGED comment: "Rust uses a global OnceLock instead of emModel/emRef"
  - emRef::Set/Reset/Get/operator-> -> Rc::clone, Option methods, direct deref via Deref trait

Coverage gaps:
  - emRefTarget as explicit base class: not replicated; Rc<T> handles refcounting internally
  - emRef::Set(ptr)/Reset() explicit rebinding: Rc uses reassignment; no explicit Set/Reset methods
  - GetRefCount(): Rc::strong_count() exists but is not commonly used in the Rust port

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - Some C++ code stores emRef<emVarModel<emRef<T>>> (nested references); the Rust equivalent pattern is not verified

